{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Dragon|type2=Flying}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Altaria}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Dragon|prevnum=333|prev=Swablu|nextnum=335|next=Zangoose|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Altaria}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Altaria\n|jname=チルタリス\n|jtranslit=Chirutarisu\n|tmname=Tyltalis\n|forme=2\n|form2=Mega Altaria\n|image2=334Altaria-Mega.png\n|mega=Altarianite\u200e\n|ndex=334\n|hdex=122\n|hdex6=127\n|sdex=172\n|u2dex=247\n|karea=Mountain\n|kdex=140\n|fbrow=197\n|abrow=260\n|type1=Dragon\n|type2=Flying\n|form2type1=Dragon\n|form2type2=Fairy\n|category=Humming\n|height-ftin=3\'07"\n|height-m=1.1\n|height-ftin2=4\'11"\n|height-m2=1.5\n|weight-lbs=45.4\n|weight-kg=20.6\n|weight-lbs2=45.4\n|weight-kg2=20.6\n|abilityn=dm\n|abilitylayout=2+1\n|abilitycolm=2\n|ability1=Natural Cure\n|abilityd=Cloud Nine\n|abilitym=Pixilate\n|egggroupn=2\n|egggroup1=Flying\n|egggroup2=Dragon\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=2\n|evsd=2\n|expyield=172\n|oldexp=188\n|lv100exp=600,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Blue\n|catchrate=45\n|body=09\n|pokefordex=altaria\n|generation=3\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Altaria\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'チルタリス\'\'\' \'\'Tyltalis\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Dragon|Flying}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation III]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Swablu}} starting at [[level]] 35. It can [[Mega Evolution|Mega Evolve]] into \'\'\'Mega Altaria\'\'\' using the [[Altarianite]].\n\n==Biology==\nAltaria is a blue, avian Pokémon. Its body and cloud-like wings are covered in fluffy, white feathers. It often folds its wings behind it, obscuring its back. Two long, blue plumes extend like streamers from the back of its head. It has a short, hooked beak and prominent cheek patches, both of which are white. Additionally, it has beady, black eyes. It has a long neck and short legs protruding from its fluffy body. The feet are blue with four toes, three claws forward and one backward. The tail is made up of five feathers, the outer two being longer than the inner ones.\n\nMega Altaria has more extensive cloud-like plumage, with a large, fluffy mass extending from its back. The feathers have grown as a self-protective measure, and they glimmer with an iridescent sheen. Its cottony wings are more distinct than in its base form, and its blue belly is now exposed. Additional fluff surrounds its neck like a collar, and its head is adorned with a hat-like crest. A single, small feather curls out from its forehead, though its facial features are unchanged. Its tail feathers have grown into a long, wavy streamer, with three longer central plumes. Mega Altaria\'s singing voice is even more beautiful than that of its regular form. It is known for its sociable personality and is not timid.<ref>http://www.pokemonrubysapphire.com/en-us/pokemon/new-mega-evolutions/mega-altaria</ref>\n\nThis Pokémon uses its wings to catch updrafts and soar across the sky. It gracefully glides through the clouds, often while singing or humming in a soprano voice. Its voice seems to have special properties which induce a dreamy state for listeners. Altaria can be very affectionate, enveloping people it has bonded with in its cotton-like wings. Altaria is often found living in {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Forest Pokémon|forests}}, though it also inhabits mountain ranges.\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Titus Altaria.png|thumb|250px|left|Altaria in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n====Major appearances====\n=====[[Winona\'s Altaria]]=====\n[[Winona]]\'s Altaria appeared in \'\'[[AG085|Sky High Gym Battle!]]\'\'. It faced off against [[Ash\'s Grovyle]] during {{Ash}}\'s [[Gym]] {{pkmn|battle}} against Winona, and lost.\n\n=====Other=====\nAn Altaria appeared in \'\'[[AG101|Vanity Affair]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Drake]]. It battled Ash\'s {{p|Grovyle}} and easily won due to its type advantage.\n\nA flock of Altaria appeared in \'\'[[AG171|Pokémon Ranger - Deoxys\' Crisis! (Part 1)]]\'\'. The Altaria\'s sense of direction had gone haywire, so [[Solana]] captured one of them with her [[Capture Styler]] to put them back in order.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Altaria appeared in \'\'[[DP156|A Meteoric Rise to Excellence!]]\'\', where it was being {{pkmn|training|trained}} by [[Wilma]]. Because of its great power, it was captured by {{TRT}}, but it managed to damage their machine to the point where it was unable to move. It was then rescued by {{AP|Gible}}.\n\nAn Altaria appeared in \'\'[[DP174|Last Call — First Round!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Nando]]. It first participated in the [[Appeal|Performance Stage]] of the [[Sinnoh Grand Festival]]. It performed alongside his {{p|Kricketot}} and helped Nando advance to the [[Contest Battle]]s.\n\nTwo Altaria appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[BW101|Drayden Versus Iris: Past, Present, and Future!]]\'\'. One of them was a Pokémon that students from the Opelucid Academy could borrow in order to learn how to battle. The other was one of the Pokémon that {{an|Iris}} had befriended.\n\nA Trainer\'s Altaria appeared in \'\'[[XY077|A Relay in the Sky!]]\'\', where it was seen participating in the [[Pokémon Sky Relay]]. [[Jessie\'s Pumpkaboo]] was found to have stowed away to take advantage and give {{TRT}} a lead in the race.\n\nAn Altaria appeared in \'\'[[XY125|A League of His Own!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Titus]]. It was used in the [[Lumiose Conference]], but was easily defeated after [[Ash\'s Greninja]] transformed into Ash-Greninja and used {{m|Water Shuriken}}.\n\nThe [[Ultra Guardians]] have a [[Poké Ride|Ride]] Altaria, which {{an|Lillie}} uses during their missions, as first seen in \'\'[[SM061|A Mission of Ultra Urgency!]]\'\'.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nMultiple Altaria debuted in \'\'[[M06|Jirachi: Wish Maker]]\'\' as some of the Pokémon that lived in [[Forina]], {{OBP|Jirachi|M06}}\'s home.\n\nMultiple Altaria made their main series debut in \'\'[[AG064|True Blue Swablu]]\'\', where they were members of the flock that an injured Swablu belonged to.\n\nAn Altaria appeared in the opening sequence of \'\'[[M07|Destiny Deoxys]]\'\'.\n\nAn Altaria made a cameo appearance in \'\'[[M08|Lucario and the Mystery of Mew]]\'\' as a resident of the [[Tree of Beginning]].\n\nAn Altaria appeared in \'\'[[AG174|New Plot, Odd Lot!]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{pkmn|Coordinator}} competing in the {{ci|Mulberry}} {{pkmn|Contest}}.\n\nMultiple Altaria appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[M09|Pokémon Ranger and the Temple of the Sea]]\'\'. They were among the Pokémon that helped {{OBP|Pokémon Ranger|Ranger series}} [[Jack Walker]] when he was a young boy lost in a blizzard.\n\nA Coordinator\'s Altaria appeared in \'\'[[DP010|Not on MY Watch Ya Don\'t!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Altaria made a brief cameo appearance in \'\'[[M11|Giratina and the Sky Warrior]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Altaria appeared in \'\'[[BW130|Butterfree and Me!]]\'\' as residents of [[Wayfarer Island]].\n\nAn Altaria that can [[Mega Evolution|Mega Evolve]] into Mega Altaria appeared in the ending segment of \'\'[[XYS02|Mega Evolution Special II]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Altaria appeared in \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\', three of which were residents of the [[Nebel Plateau]].\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Hoenn}}\n{{Animedexbody|AG064|Altaria|Ash\'s Pokédex|Altaria, the Humming Pokémon. Altaria is the evolved form of {{p|Swablu}}. It uses its fluffy wings to catch updrafts and is known for its beautiful {{m|Sing|high-pitched song}}.}}\n{{Animedexbody|AG085|Altaria|May\'s Pokédex|Altaria, the Humming Pokémon. Altaria glides up into the sky using its wings like sails to catch rising breezes.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Advanced Generation\'\'|Hoenn}}\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP156|Altaria|Dawn\'s Pokédex|Altaria, the Humming Pokémon and the evolved form of Swablu. As Altaria flies across the sky, it resembles a soft cloud. It hums using its high voice.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n\n===In the Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire Animated Trailer===\n[[File:Mega Altaria ORAS Trailer.png|thumb|250px|Mega Altaria in the animated trailer]]\nA [[Mega Evolution|Mega]] Altaria appeared in the [[Pokémon Omega Ruby and Pokémon Alpha Sapphire Animated Trailer]], under the ownership of {{ga|May}}. It was seen participating in a {{pkmn|Contest|Pokémon Contest Spectacular}} alongside May and Mega {{p|Audino}}.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Winona Altaria Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Altaria in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pocket Monsters BW: Good Partners manga===\nMultiple Altaria appeared in a flashback in [[BWGP03]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n{{main|Winona\'s Altaria}}\n[[Winona]] of the Fortree Gym has an Altaria as her main Pokémon, much as in the games. It was briefly seen carrying Winona and [[Flannery]] to the [[Weather Institute]] after [[Norman]]\'s battle with {{adv|Ruby}} in \'\'[[PS211|Hanging Around With Slaking III]]\'\', but wasn\'t seen fighting until \'\'[[PS226|I Dare Ya, Altaria... Knock Chic off My Shoulder]]\'\', where it fought {{adv|Sapphire}}\'s [[Chic]] and managed to win even after the latter evolved into a {{p|Blaziken}}.\n\nAn Altaria was one of {{adv|Ruby}}\'s opponents in the Normal Rank Beauty Contest in [[Verdanturf Town]] in \'\'[[PS217|Mind-Boggling with Medicham]]\'\'.\n\n[[Lisia]] also owns an Altaria nicknamed Ali, who first appeared in \'\'[[PAORAS00|Omega Alpha Adventure 0]]\'\'.\n\nIn \'\'[[PAORAS04|Omega Alpha Adventure 4]]\'\', an Altaria appeared as silhouetted during {{Steven}}\'s explanation about the [[Draconid people]].\n\nAn Altaria appeared in \'\'[[PAORAS16|Omega Alpha Adventure 16]]\'\' under the ownership of {{adv|Wally}}.\n\n===In the Pokémon - The Legend of the Dragon King manga===\nAn Altaria appeared in Pokémon - The Legend of the Dragon King.\n