n Mega Altaria\'s head may draw inspiration from {{wp|ushanka}}s.\n\n====Name origin====\nAltaria is a combination of \'\'{{wp|alto}}\'\' (Spanish, Portuguese, and Italian for \'\'high\'\') or \'\'altus\'\' (Latin for \'\'high\'\') and \'\'aria\'\' (Italian for \'\'air\'\'). \'\'{{wp|Aria}}\'\' in music can refer to expressive melody, relating to Altaria\'s singing abilities. "Ria" could additionally be a misspelling of {{wp|Rhea}}, the name of a large white bird. It may also refer to the star {{wp|Altair}}, the brightest star in the constellation {{wp|Aquila (constellation)|Aquila}}, the Eagle.\n\nTyltalis may refer to \'\'{{wp|Epsilon Draconis|Tyl}}\'\'—also known as Epsilon Draconis—a star in the constellation {{wp|Draco (constellation)|Draco}}, the Dragon. It may also be a reference to the play \'\'L\'Oiseau Bleu\'\' (\'\'{{wp|The Blue Bird (play)|The Blue Bird}}\'\') by Belgian playwright {{wp|Maurice Maeterlinck}}. The story is about two siblings, Mytyl and Tyltyl (ミチル \'\'Michiru\'\' and チルチル \'\'Chiruchiru\'\' in the Japanese translation of the play), who are tasked with finding the "blue bird of happiness."\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Dragon|type2=Flying\n|ja=チルタリス \'\'Tyltalis\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'{{wp|Epsilon Draconis|Tyl}}\'\' and \'\'Tyltyl\'\'\n|fr=Altaria|frmeaning=Same as English name\n|es=Altaria|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Altaria|demeaning=Same as English name\n|it=Altaria|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=파비코리 \'\'Pavicori\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|파비코 \'\'Pabiko\'\'|Swablu}}, {{tt|파랑\'\'parang\'\'|blue}}, {{tt|파랑새 \'\'Parangsae\'\'|\'\'dollarbird\'\' or the play \'\'L\'Oiseau Bleu\'\'}}, and possibly a corruption of \'\'beak\'\' and {{tt|꼬리 \'\'kkori\'\'|tail}}\n|zh_cmn=七夕青鳥 / 七夕青鸟 \'\'Qīxìqīngniǎo\'\' |zh_cmnmeaning=From {{wp|Qixi Festival|七夕 \'\'Qīxì\'\'}} and {{tt|青鳥 \'\'Qīngniǎo\'\'|\'\'blue bird\'\' or the play \'\'L\'Oiseau Bleu\'\'}}. The Qixi Festival originated from the tale of {{wp|The Weaver Girl and the Cowherd}}, a love story featuring two characters symbolized by the stars {{wp|Altair}} and {{wp|Vega}}.\n|zh_yue=七夕青鳥 \'\'Chātjihkchēngníuh\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=Same as Mandarin name\n|hi=अल्टारीआ \'\'Altaria\'\'|himeaning=Transliteration of English name\n|ru=Алтария \'\'Altariya\'\'|rumeaning=Transliteration of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Winona\'s Altaria]]\n\n==Notes==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Dragon|type2=Flying}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Dragon|prevnum=333|prev=Swablu|nextnum=335|next=Zangoose}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Shadow Pokémon in Pokémon XD]]\n\n[[de:Altaria]]\n[[es:Altaria]]\n[[fr:Altaria]]\n[[it:Altaria]]\n[[ja:チルタリス]]\n[[zh:七夕青鸟]]'}